Raw dev notes -- WAHA Monitor: Building a WhatsApp Intelligence System (March 2026)

My WAHA monitor project exploded in scope this month. What started as a simple WhatsApp
group monitor turned into a full intelligence pipeline: message forwarding, daily AI digests,
newsletter ingestion, Docker hardening, and a lot of crash recovery.

Major features built:
- Daily AI digest via Gemini: summarizes all monitored WhatsApp groups
- Halacha digest: separate pipeline for religious content with dedup against previous digests
- Email newsletter ingest via Gmail IMAP polling
- Medium article pipeline: Gemini filter + Freedium fetch + TOON compression
- Auto-forward digest to WhatsApp groups with randomized timing
- Shabbat-aware scheduling (skip Fri 16:00 - Sat 21:00 Israel time)
- Reminder system with persistence across container restarts
- Pushover push notifications + QR code recovery on WhatsApp logout

Operational hardening:
- Docker watchdog with crash forensics, disk/WAL/memory checks
- Escalating Docker recovery (restart -> unregister WSL)
- Non-blocking startup catch-up with forward lock
- ChromaDB dedup: removed 2268 duplicate messages
- Security: bound all ports to localhost only
- Weekly group name refresh instead of startup-only

Struggles:
- WAHA has 6 permanently failing groups with no upstream fix
- Docker Desktop crashes required auto-restart detection
- Sleep prevention on Windows was harder than expected (Modern Standby issues)
- Digest catch-up after downtime needed careful checkpoint logic

The system now runs 24/7 on my Windows machine with Docker, monitoring dozens of groups,
filtering Medium articles, ingesting newsletters, and sending daily summaries. It's become
my personal information hub.

Next: Raspberry Pi migration, admin API endpoints, Voyage embeddings.
